Since 2005, civil rights activists have been returning to Moore's Ford Bridge to mimic the night when two black couples - Roger and Dorothy Malcom as well as George and Mae Murray Dorsey - were lynched by the Ku Klux Klan in 1946.
No one has ever been charged with the murders.
