Role backwards: The city sets 46 kitchen aids
The city organizes the kita lunch table itself again.
With fixed contacts for the children and an assignment to the team.
The clock is turned back in the city’s daycare centers.
On 1 September, the city of Krefeld will take over the food supply in the urban daycare facilities (Kitas) again on its own.
For Sonja Pommeranz, Deputy Head of Youth Aid, this is good news: "We were all very happy".
Cooking continues outside the house: a caterer takes over this task and delivers freshly cooked cooled.
The city runs 46 day care centers in the Krefeld area, in 44 the children get a warm meal at lunchtime.
In the past year, 2,800 children were sitting at the tables, and the demand was growing steadily.
"In the meantime, not only children who are cared for 45 hours a week eat lunch in the nursery," explains Pommeranz.
"The offer is also valid in 35-hour care if children stay until 2 p.m.."
46 part-time workers have kitchen service from 1 September: they heat the delivered food, supplement it with salad, raw food and fruit, portion the meal individually, give out the food, clean, rinse and clean the kitchen.
“The employees are firmly assigned to a nursery,” says Pommeranz.
The size - there are two-group as well as seven-group facilities - decides the scope of the hours.
"The kitchen helpers are now firmly part of the Kita team," says Pommeranz satisfied.
"In this way, they are much more involved and it is easier for the nursery guidance to implement educational concepts."
This is also what it is all about: healthy eating and cooking lessons.
“Children should help prepare the food.”
The direct connection of the kitchen power to the team makes sense.
Also for the children.
"They have a known power in the nursery, a person who is familiar to them, and not constantly changing people."
This continuity is important for the children.
The cleaning of the nursery rooms - so far also the task of the kitchen staff - will in future be done by special cleaning staff.
This variant - the separation of cleaning and kitchen service - has in addition to the quality improvement of kitchen performance also the charm, which it has proven to be the most economical in comparison between self-direction and external allocation for the city, according to the press office.
And that even though 46 part-time workers are being re-employed.
"But these hours are not so important for around 750 people in the education sector," says Sonja Pommeranz.
Afghan democracy depends on women’s political role, UN says
Elections can only be representative if all members of society, including women, play a role, the head of the UN mission in Afghanistan said on Wednesday.
Nicholas Haysom, acting head of the United Nations mission, said hundreds of women will run in the provincial council elections, with three women running for the role of vice president and more than 30 percent of newly registered voters being women.
“The role of women cannot be overestimated,” he said in a statement on Wednesday.
Elections can only be truly representative and credible if women participate fully and are involved in all parts of the electoral process.
Afghan elections for the provincial council and the presidential elections will take place on 5 April.
The Taliban have released threats against an election process that coincide with the transition from international combat to an advisory role.
This year, for the first time, the elections will pass power peacefully from one democratically elected government to the next.
Haysom said a strong role for women will reinforce Afghanistan’s democratic success.
The Afghan Independent Election Commission reports that 1.2 million women out of a total of 3.6 million registered voters have been registered.
