Interview: "Domspatzen report relieves Pope Brother Georg Ratzinger"
The Regensburg Domspatzen report on the abuse cases relieves Pope Brother Georg Ratzinger.
Author and historian Michael Hesemann.
The final report on the abuse scandal at the Regensburg Domspatzen continues to lead to discussions.
Christian Weisnder, spokesman for the reform movement "Wir sind Kirche", after publication to the German press agency, said he expects an apology from the former Regensburg bishop and present-day Cardinal Gerhard Ludwig Müller as well as from Domkapellmeister Georg Ratzinger, the 93-year-old brother of emeritus Pope Benedict XVI.
